ults\n   ‚úď Save checkpoints frequently\n   ‚úď Use descriptive variable names\n   ‚úď Add assertions to validate assumptions\n\n5. Error Handling\n   ‚úď Use try-except blocks for robustness\n   ‚úď Log errors with full context\n   ‚úď Don&#39;t ignore warnings - investigate them\n   ‚úď Validate assumptions with assertions\n   ‚úď Handle edge cases gracefully\n\n6. Iterative Development\n   ‚úď Start small - validate on tiny dataset first\n   ‚úď Gradually scale up\n   ‚úď Monitor resource usage\n   ‚úď Checkpoint before long-running operations\n   ‚úď Document deviations from plan\n\nBEST PRACTICES:\n\n‚úď DO: Start small and validate incrementally\n‚úď DO: Print shapes and statistics frequently\n‚úď DO: Visualize intermediate results\n‚úď DO: Save outputs incrementally (don&#39;t wait until end)\n‚úď DO: Make experiments reproducible (random seeds, versions)\n‚úď DO: Comment complex logic immediately\n‚úď DO: Separate data processing, modeling, and evaluation\n\n‚úó DON&#39;T: Hardcode paths or magic numbers\n‚úó DON&#39;T: Skip validation steps\n‚úó DON&#39;T: Ignore failed assertions or warnings\n‚úó DON&#39;T: Run long experiments without checkpointing\n‚úó DON&#39;T: Proceed if results look wrong - investigate first\n\nREPRODUCIBILITY CHECKLIST:\n\n```python\n# Always set random seeds at the start\nimport random\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef set_seed(seed=42):\n    random.seed(seed)\n    np.random.seed(seed)\n    # Add framework-specific seeds (PyTorch, TensorFlow, etc.)\n\nset_seed(42)\n\n# Log environment\nimport sys\nprint(f&#34;Python: {sys.version}&#34;)\nprint(f&#34;NumPy: {np.__version__}&#34;)\n# Add other relevant library versions\n\n# Save configuration\nconfig = {\n    &#39;seed&#39;: 42,\n    &#39;dataset&#39;: &#39;dataset_name&#39;,\n    &#39;hyperparameters&#39;: {...},\n    &#39;timestamp&#39;: datetime.now().isoformat()\n}\nimport json\nwith open(&#39;results/config.json&#39;, &#39;w&#39;) as f:\n    json.dump(config, f, indent=2)\n```\n\n‚ēź‚